---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout 
	title="ELRS Mobile | Flash & Configure ExpressLRS from your Phone" 
	description="Flash and configure ExpressLRS receivers and transmitters directly from your iOS or Android device. 100% offline flashing, no PC or cables required."
>
	<main>
		<section class="hero">
			<h1 class="hero-gradient">The Field-Ready ExpressLRS Tool.<br/>No Laptop Required.</h1>
			<p>Flash V3.x and V4.x Firmware via Wi-Fi directly from your iOS or Android device.</p>
			
			{/* 
			<div class="hero-visual">
				<img src="/images/hero-iphone-radio.png" alt="ELRS Mobile on iPhone next to a RadioMaster Radio" class="hero-image" />
			</div>
			*/}

			<div class="cta-buttons">
				<a
					href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=io.datarx.elrsmobile"
					class="btn primary">Get it on Google Play</a
				>
				<a
					href="https://testflight.apple.com/join/jwU1WrpX"
					class="btn secondary">Join iOS TestFlight</a
				>
			</div>

			<div class="cta-secondary">
				<a href="/user_guide" class="secondary-link">Documentation</a>
				<span class="divider">|</span>
				<a
					href="https://github.com/wbhinton/ELRS-Mobile"
					class="secondary-link">Project GitHub</a
				>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section id="problem-solution" class="problem-solution">
			<h2>Stuck at the field? No cell service?</h2>
			<div class="feature-highlight">
				<div class="highlight-text">
					<p>
						We've all been there: You're at the race or the park, and you realize your TX is on 4.0 but your RX is still on 3.x. Without a laptop and internet, your day is over.
					</p>
					<p>
						<strong>ELRS Mobile solves this with Offline Caching.</strong> Once you've cached a firmware version at home, the app compiles and flashes every supported target completely offline. No laptop, no hassle, just more flight time.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="features">
			<div class="feature-card">
				<h3>⚡ Blazing Fast</h3>
				<p>Flash from local cache instead of waiting for web downloads.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<h3>📡 Reliable Anywhere</h3>
				<p>Eliminate edge cases with zero cell coverage or wifi access. Connection resilience ensures you stay connected during transient network drops.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<h3>🛠 Unified Flow</h3>
				<p>One interface for all your ExpressLRS hardware needs. Automatically patches firmware with your unique SSID and Binding Phrase before flashing OTA.</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="demo">
			<h2>See it in Action</h2>
			<p class="demo-sub">Watch the ELRS Mobile Flashing Demo by 828Engineer</p>
			<div class="video-container">
				<div class="phone-mockup">
					<iframe
						width="100%"
						height="100%"
						src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/6tukOoXa5aQ"
						title="ELRS Mobile Flashing Demo"
						frameborder="0"
						allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
						allowfullscreen
					>
					</iframe>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>



		<section id="installation">
			<h2>Installation</h2>
			
			<div class="installation-type">
				<h3>Recommended: Official App Stores</h3>
				<p>For the most seamless experience and automatic updates, install via official channels.</p>
				<div class="store-grid">
					<a
						href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=io.datarx.elrsmobile"
						class="store-card"
					>
						<div class="store-icon">
							<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"
								><path
									d="M17.523 15.3414L20.355 13.706C21.215 13.209 21.215 11.961 20.355 11.464L17.523 9.82944L14.771 12.5834L17.523 15.3414ZM13.883 13.4724L16.635 16.2234L5.656 22.564C5.071 22.902 4.331 22.795 3.865 22.28L13.883 13.4724ZM3.535 20.916L12.997 12.5844L3.535 4.25144C3.195 4.41444 3 4.76744 3 5.16644V20.0014C3 20.4 3.195 20.7534 3.535 20.916ZM13.883 11.6964L3.865 2.88844C4.331 2.37344 5.071 2.26644 5.656 2.60444L16.635 8.94544L13.883 11.6964Z"
								></path>
							</svg>
						</div>
						<div class="store-info">
							<h3>Google Play</h3>
							<span class="status">Production</span>
						</div>
					</a>
					<a
						href="https://testflight.apple.com/join/jwU1WrpX"
						class="store-card"
					>
						<div class="store-icon">
							<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"
								><path
									d="M17.05 20.28c-.96.95-2.06 1.92-3.4 1.92s-1.8-.84-3.37-.84-2.1.84-3.41.84c-1.28 0-2.43-1.02-3.41-2.45-2.17-3.17-3.26-7.44-1.17-10.73 1-1.5 2.51-2.48 4.14-2.48 1.4 0 2.4 1.05 3.4 1.05s2.2-.9 3.55-.9c1.1 0 2.45.6 3.45 1.7-2.7 1.6-2.2 5.3 0 6.6-.7 1.8-1.7 3.6-2.94 5.16zM13 2c0 1.5-1.26 3.1-2.9 3.1-.15-1.9 1.4-3.5 2.9-3.5z"
								></path>
							</svg>
						</div>
						<div class="store-info">
							<h3>TestFlight</h3>
							<span class="status">In Review for App Store</span>
						</div>
					</a>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="installation-advanced">
				<h3>Advanced: Sideloading & Manual Installs</h3>
				<p>For power users or local development, download the latest artifacts directly.</p>
				<div class="advanced-links">
					<a href="https://github.com/wbhinton/ELRS-Mobile/releases" class="advanced-card">
						<h4>Download Android APK</h4>
						<p>Sideload directly from GitHub Releases</p>
					</a>
					<a href="https://github.com/wbhinton/ELRS-Mobile" class="advanced-card">
						<h4>View Source Code</h4>
						<p>Build from source or contribute on GitHub</p>
					</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section id="hardware">
			<h2>Supported Hardware & Versions</h2>
			<p>
				ELRS Mobile is optimized for high-speed Wi-Fi flashing across current ExpressLRS generations (V3.x and V4.x).
			</p>
			<div class="hardware-grid">
				<div class="hw-card">
					<h4>Supported Chipsets</h4>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>ESP8285</strong> (Common on RXs)</li>
						<li><strong>ESP32</strong> (Standard TX/RX)</li>
						<li><strong>ESP32-C3</strong> (Next-Gen)</li>
						<li><strong>ESP32-S3</strong> (High-Performance)</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="hw-card">
					<h4>Tested Targets</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>RadioMaster XR1 / XR4 Dual Band</li>
						<li>BETAFPV SuperP 14Ch (2.4G & 900M)</li>
						<li>HappyModel EP / EP Dual</li>
						<li>RadioMaster Nomad / Pocket</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
			<p class="note">
				Currently unsupported: STM32 targets requiring serial STLink or
				Betaflight Passthrough.
			</p>
		</section>





		<div class="docs-link">
			<p>Want to see how it works under the hood? Check out the <a href="/user_guide">Official Documentation</a>.</p>
		</div>

		<footer>
			<p>&copy; 2026 Weston Hinton. Distributed under the GNU GPL v3.</p>
			<p class="legal-notice">
				ELRS Mobile is a free and open-source (FOSS) project developed independently by Weston Hinton. 
				This project is not an official product of ExpressLRS LLC and is not officially supported, endorsed, or certified by the ExpressLRS development team.
			</p>
			<p class="trademark-notice">
				ExpressLRS and the ExpressLRS logo are trademarks of ExpressLRS LLC. Use of these marks on this website is for descriptive and compatibility purposes only. 
				For the official ExpressLRS configurator and documentation, please visit <a href="https://www.expresslrs.org">expresslrs.org</a>.
			</p>
			<div class="support-notice">
				<p>
					Support the official ExpressLRS project: 
					<a href="https://opencollective.com/expresslrs/donate?interval=oneTime&amount=20&name=&legalName=&email=" class="support-link">Donate via Open Collective</a>
				</p>
			</div>
			<p>
				<a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
			</p>
		</footer>
	</main>
</Layout>

<script>
	document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
		const playStoreLinks = document.querySelectorAll('a[href*="play.google.com/store/apps/details"]');
		const testFlightLinks = document.querySelectorAll('a[href*="testflight.apple.com/join"]');

		playStoreLinks.forEach(link => {
			link.addEventListener('click', () => {
				if (typeof window.gtag === 'function') {
					window.gtag('event', 'app_store_click', {
						'app_store': 'Google Play',
						'event_category': 'App Install',
						'event_label': 'Play Store Link'
					});
				}
			});
		});

		testFlightLinks.forEach(link => {
			link.addEventListener('click', () => {
				if (typeof window.gtag === 'function') {
					window.gtag('event', 'app_store_click', {
						'app_store': 'TestFlight',
						'event_category': 'App Install',
						'event_label': 'TestFlight Link'
					});
				}
			});
		});
	});
</script>

<style>
